---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="RFC: message tool" description="Explicit reply contract via a message() tool. Resolves thinking-as-reply at the design level.">

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 pt-16 md:pt-20 pb-16">

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <p class="text-amber-400 font-medium mb-2">2026-05-21 · Draft, awaiting Diego's review</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-black text-white leading-tight mb-4">
        RFC: <code class="text-amber-300 bg-navy-800/60 px-2 py-1 rounded">message</code> tool
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
        Make the user-facing reply explicit. Anything the model wants Diego to see goes through a <code class="text-amber-300">message()</code> tool call; everything else stays internal. Resolves the thinking-as-reply class of bugs at the design level instead of post-hoc regex.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Meta -->
    <div class="mb-12 p-4 bg-navy-800/60 border border-navy-600/50 rounded-lg text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
      <p class="mb-1"><span class="text-white font-semibold">Targets:</span> <code class="text-amber-300">raw_runner.py</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">cron_runner.py</code>, all orienters, all cron prompts.</p>
      <p class="mb-1"><span class="text-white font-semibold">Related:</span> thinking-as-reply incident 14 may; bedtime-story log mess 20 may; cuentos heads-up incident 19 may.</p>
      <p><span class="text-white font-semibold">Inspired by:</span> OpenClaw release patterns (May 2026), message_tool opt-in (Fixes #81598).</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Problem -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-navy-600">Problem</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Today the user-facing reply is <strong class="text-white">implicit</strong>: whatever text the model produces in its final assistant block is sent to Telegram. This conflates four different things the model legitimately does:</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 text-gray-300">
      <li><strong class="text-white">Reasoning</strong> ("let me check the log, the model probably did X")</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Tool narration</strong> ("voy a tirar grep ahora")</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Intermediate findings</strong> ("ok, encontrado el bug")</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">The actual reply</strong> ("hecho, esto era. ¿siguiente?")</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">The model is told via orienter "your raw text goes to Telegram", so it tries to filter (3) and (4) from (1) and (2) by force of will. It mostly succeeds, but:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-300">
      <li><strong class="text-white">Long tool chains drift</strong> (Pass-B in cuentos, "I have the full picture" in bedtime-story 20 may).</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Filter regex is fragile</strong> — 6 fires since 15 may, 3 of them false positives suppressing legitimate replies. Diego sees "Perdona, se me ha mezclado el razonamiento" when the reply was fine.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Crons have no filter at all</strong> because <code class="text-amber-300">cron_runner.py</code> doesn't share the safety net.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Multi-message turns are unnatural</strong> — model has to cram start + middle + end into a single final text, or use the progress-bar script imperatively.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Proposal -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-navy-600">Proposal</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Add an explicit <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> tool. Anything the model wants the user to see goes through this tool. Anything else (reasoning, internal tool narration) stays invisible.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-8 mb-3">Tool contract (draft)</h3>
    <pre class="bg-navy-900 border border-navy-600 rounded-lg p-4 overflow-x-auto text-sm text-gray-300 mb-6"><code>{`{
  "name": "message",
  "description": "Send a user-facing message. Anything you DO NOT call this tool with stays internal to your reasoning.",
  "input_schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "required": ["text"],
    "properties": {
      "text": { "type": "string" },
      "action": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["send", "edit", "delete"],
        "default": "send"
      },
      "message_id": { "type": "integer" },
      "kind": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": ["reply", "progress", "ack"],
        "default": "reply"
      }
    }
  }
}`}</code></pre>

    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-8 mb-3">Runner behaviour change</h3>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-2"><strong class="text-white">Before:</strong> <code class="text-amber-300">raw_runner</code> extracts <code class="text-amber-300">text</code> from the last assistant block, sends as Telegram message.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4"><strong class="text-white">After:</strong> <code class="text-amber-300">raw_runner</code> sends nothing by default. Each <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> tool call → Telegram action. Tool returns <code class="text-amber-300">{"{ ok: true, message_id: N }"}</code> so the model can chain edit/delete.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-8 mb-3">Turn ends with NO <code>message</code> call — policy?</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-4 text-gray-300">
      <li><strong class="text-white">(A) Strict.</strong> Send nothing. Log a warning. Model is responsible.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">(B) Fallback.</strong> If turn ends with no message call AND the final block has text, send it as before (legacy path).</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">(C) Hybrid.</strong> Like A in interactive chats; like B in crons (because cron prompts will take time to migrate).</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-6">My recommendation: <strong class="text-white">(C) Hybrid</strong>, switching to A globally once all crons are migrated.</p>

    <!-- Open Questions — the important section -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-amber-500">⚠️ Open questions for Diego</h2>
    <p class="text-gray-400 italic mb-6">These need your call before I implement. Each has my recommendation.</p>
    <ol class="space-y-4 mb-8 text-gray-300 list-decimal list-inside marker:text-amber-400 marker:font-bold">
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Tool naming.</strong> <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> is generic. Alternatives: <code class="text-amber-300">say</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">reply</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">tell_user</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">notify</code>.
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> (matches Telegram terminology, matches the existing tg-progress script).</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Edit/delete in scope from day 1?</strong> Or ship send-only first and add edit later?
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: ship <code class="text-amber-300">send</code> only in v1. Add <code class="text-amber-300">edit</code>/<code class="text-amber-300">delete</code> in v1.1 when we replace the progress-bar shell-out.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Per-message <code class="text-amber-300">kind</code>?</strong> Is <code class="text-amber-300">kind=reply|progress|ack</code> useful, or premature?
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: drop it from v1. Add when we know what behaviour differs.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Fallback policy.</strong> A, B, or C above?
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: C during migration, A once stable.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Files/audio/images via this tool?</strong> Today those go via <code class="text-amber-300">telegram-send-file.py</code> and <code class="text-amber-300">tts-send.py</code> bash scripts.
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: keep separate for v1. Don't bundle.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Migration order.</strong> Interactive chats first (raw_runner) then crons? Or vice versa?
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: raw_runner first — where the filter lives today, immediate value.</span>
      </li>
      <li class="leading-relaxed">
        <strong class="text-white">Telemetry.</strong> Should <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> calls show up in per-turn telemetry (<code class="text-amber-300">elapsed_ms</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">reply_chars</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">tool_calls</code>)?
        <span class="block mt-1 text-gray-400 text-sm pl-6">My lean: yes, log <code class="text-amber-300">message_calls</code> count + total chars.</span>
      </li>
    </ol>

    <!-- Implementation plan -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-navy-600">Implementation plan</h2>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-6 mb-2">Phase 1 (raw_runner, this weekend)</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-4 text-gray-300">
      <li>Add <code class="text-amber-300">message</code> to tool registry, gated by env flag <code class="text-amber-300">RAW_RUNNER_MESSAGE_TOOL=1</code>.</li>
      <li>Implement send-only (no edit/delete yet).</li>
      <li>Fallback policy = B during transition.</li>
      <li>Test against Workshop topic only.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-6 mb-2">Phase 2 (orienter rewrite, ~3 days after Phase 1)</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-4 text-gray-300">
      <li>Update orienter to teach the model the new contract.</li>
      <li>Update SOUL.md "Communication Style" section.</li>
      <li>Flip flag globally for interactive chats. Keep fallback B for crons.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-6 mb-2">Phase 3 (cron migration, weeks 2–4)</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-4 text-gray-300">
      <li>One cron at a time. Order: <code class="text-amber-300">bedtime-story</code>, <code class="text-amber-300">morning-briefing</code>, then rest.</li>
      <li>Each cron's prompt updated to call <code class="text-amber-300">message()</code>. Once migrated, fallback → A.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-amber-400 mt-6 mb-2">Phase 4 (cleanup, week 5)</h3>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-6 text-gray-300">
      <li>Remove the thinking-as-reply regex filter entirely.</li>
      <li>Remove legacy text-as-reply path from runner.</li>
      <li>Switch fallback to A globally.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Risks -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-navy-600">Risks &amp; mitigations</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 mb-6 text-gray-300">
      <li><strong class="text-white">Silent regression in crons.</strong> Watchdog rule: "cron run completed without any <code class="text-amber-300">message()</code> call" → alert to Workshop.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Orienter bloat.</strong> ~300 tokens per turn for contract description. Put it in cached static prefix of system prompt.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Model forgets to call the tool.</strong> Explicit examples in orienter, plus fallback B during transition.</li>
      <li><strong class="text-white">Migration drag.</strong> 22 productive crons need their prompts updated. Phased, only touch a cron when already misbehaving.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Out of scope -->
    <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white mt-12 mb-4 pb-2 border-b border-navy-600">Out of scope for v1</h2>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1 mb-6 text-gray-300">
      <li>File/audio/image bundling (separate tools).</li>
      <li>Cross-chat messaging.</li>
      <li>Scheduled/delayed messages.</li>
      <li>Reactions, replies-to-specific-messages.</li>
    </ul>

    <!-- Decision point -->
    <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-amber-500/10 border border-amber-500/30 rounded-lg">
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-amber-300 mb-2">Decision point</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-200 leading-relaxed">Diego: review the 7 open questions above. Once answered, I implement Phase 1 against Workshop this weekend.</p>
    </div>

  </section>
</Layout>
